Mentally I’m here 😌 but IRL I’m home with a little cold I caught in Tallahassee. Nevertheless it was a fun weekend in my old stomping grounds! 😜
Guys I’m going to SCOTLAND in 10 DAYS!! 😍 that’s where my head is at rn 😄I’m so thrilled to be taking this trip with a couple of my mer-besties! Now which tail do I bring??? 😅

Time to go wherever the wind (or current) takes me. 😌 Today I get to cross a new country off my bucket list! I just landed in SCOTLAND and it is beautiful!! I’m so grateful to be traveling abroad with my friends! 🥰 The pandemic kept us locked down for far too long and I’m just so happy to be FREE again! Follow along in my stories to explore Scotland with me over the next two weeks!

Scotland was a dream! 🤩 I spent the last couple of weeks hiking through snowy mountains, playing in the rivers of iced over waterfalls, prancing down the halls of gorgeous castles, climbing through old ruins, and exploring quaint towns and bustling cities! I hitched a ride on Nessie and spotted unicorns everywhere! 🦄 🏰 Scotland was absolutely magical, but now I’m happy to be home where the baths are always hot and the weather is, too! 😌 Ps I hope you guys love the new @finfolkproductions “Riverbend” mermaid tail as much as I do! 💚 cover photo by @thestorey

My besties are huge outlander fans so we stayed near some scenes from the show when traveling through Scotland. This Queens suite was one of the cooler rooms I stayed in with a bath tub in the bedroom and a view of the gothic style buildings out front! 😍 Do you watch the show? 🏰🧜🏼‍♀️🛁🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿

Find someone who will travel the world and play mermaids with you! Happy [belated] birthday to my merbestie @treasure.coast.mermaid! 🧜🏼‍♀️❤️ This girl loves to shop, adventure, drink tea & eat good food, and overall have a good time! We clicked over mermaiding but I’m so grateful that our friendship has grown way beyond the waters we met in! 🌊 The first photo is from our recent trip to Scotland last month and the second is from our 2020 London trip! 🛁💚 cheers to another year around the sun for you!

Tell me you had the best birthday ever without telling me you had the best birthday ever… Gabby will go first! 😍🧜🏼‍♀️💖 Today I got to surprise the sweetest little mermaid-lover! We put on tattoos and played some games, then she taught me all about cheerleading and even had me spot her for some tricks in the pool 😂 So blessed to do what I love - and experience things other humans love! 📣

I love my mermaid tail! 🧜🏼‍♀️ The colors, the shape, the way she swims- she’s absolutely PERFECT! 😍 Dare I say the best mermaid tail ever?? To me- yes! But there are SO many styles of tails out there, I wish I could have them all! 

I get asked about my silicone tail all the time, and I have a ton of posts on my blog that detail my @finfolkproductions tail throughly- but I’d love to offer a resource that reviews and features as many tail makers & mermaids in the community as possible. So if you have a silicone mermaid tail that you absolutely LOVE- fill out the form in my IG story highlight “BEST TAIL” for a chance to be featured! 🧜🏼‍♀️💦

How’s that for live action?? 😜 I loved the new little mermaid movie!! They added so many cute new moments & details (but they also left out a few of my favorites- my poopsies!! 😭) Have you seen it yet, and if so what did you think of it? 🫧

My happy place is at the bottom of the ocean 🫧🧜🏼‍♀️🪸 I’m so happy to be back in the water now that things are warming up! My husband filmed this about 2 weeks ago on our dive together. Conditions were perfect underwater but a storm was brewing on the surface… luckily we managed to pack up and paddle in before the rain came!

If you’re new here, welcome! And I mean that, you are always welcomed in the mer community! 💕 You’ll come to find that we’re generally a pretty open minded bunch, happy and eager to help build each other up! 🧜🏼‍♀️ if you find yourself feeling like you don’t belong where the people are, maybe try putting on a mermaid tail & see what it’s all about! 😜

𝐈 𝐁𝐎𝐔𝐆𝐇𝐓 𝐀 𝐇𝐎𝐔𝐒𝐄!! 🏠 I am so flipping proud to say that I am now a 𝒉𝒐𝒎𝒆𝒐𝒘𝒏𝒆𝒓! Under the sea will always be my ocean home, but it will be so lovely to finally have a place to dry off my fins and enjoy all the human things! So if you’ve been asking “where’d you go?” Let’s just say buying a home takes a LOT of energy and I would’ve simply drowned trying to post at my normal rate. 😝🫧

That being said, a LOT has happened this year! I am sitting on so much content (like today’s new clip), and so many big announcements & opportunities, I can’t wait to share them all with you soon! 🧜🏼‍♀️💕

Summer mermaid memories I will never forget! 🥹 Don’t get me wrong I LOVE performing, but I’m most fulfilled by the places and faces mermaiding has brought me! I’m so grateful for my merbesties and a welcoming community! 🥰 
This “new” clip is from last summer’s trip to the keys with @treasure.coast.mermaid and her husband @thestorey, who is filming! We met up with @barefoot_bythesea for the first time and of course we played mermaids together! After, we transformed into humans and explored a fort on land- a successful day in my books!

Last week I stumbled upon my first octopus’s garden- dyk it’s a real thing?? 😱 I was swimming out to the reef on the water’s surface when I spotted a small pile of white shells and broken looking bits among the dark rocks. I dove straight down to the ocean’s floor, noticing first a broken crab claw just a few inches from the rubble. My heart raced with the thought that this could be one!! 🐚 

As I looked up towards the rest of the pile something else caught my eye: two octopus eyes peering back at me from under a rock! 🐙 

Octopuses feel safest in their den, and therefor choose to bring their meals home to eat. Over time, piles of prey-remains build up just outside their homes, which we’ve innocently deemed octopus’s gardens! 😅 These beautiful shell gardens may have a morbid history but it sure was thrilling to find one with the octopus still home! I’ve seen octopus while diving before but this was my first time getting invited over for a garden party! 🤭 have you ever seen an octopus IRL?

Today marks my 3 year anniversary as a Finfolk Ambassador! 3 years of mermaid tail unboxings, fantasy photoshoots, & underwater adventures! And to think 8 years ago when I started mermaiding I told myself I was only going to get ONE tail 🤭 silly me! I still get giddy every time I get a new Finfolk package in… and guess what! One came in today!! 😱 can you guess my next tail color? It’s unlike ANY tail I’ve had before! 😍

Barbie was right: if you can dream it, you can be it!! 🧜🏼‍♀️💖 This is your daily reminder to GO FOR IT! Whatever you’re dreaming about can be yours and I want it to be! I’m rooting for you, and the universe is, too! Do all the exploring you can, try as many new things as possible and say yes to the opportunities that swim your way! 💦

Dancing the night away in my new HOUSE! Over the weekend @giraffe_adventurer & I moved into our new home- yes, we’re still in South Florida thankfully & we love absolutely it here!! We took a break from unpacking this morning and caught 18 lobsters diving off our local beach with my dad, so we’ll be eating good tonight (& for weeks to come! 😜) There’s still lots of settling in to do at our house, but this happy dance can’t stop, won’t stop!! 💃🏻 I love my new home!! 🏠

Visiting the local reefs in my backyard always puts me in my feels! 🪸🐠🥹 The ocean is so full of magic, it’s hard for me to believe some humans will go their whole lives without ever setting foot in it! 😱

Little me would be sooo proud 🥹 I finally earned my YouTube Play button! I’ve been ‘content creating’ since the 90’s, or as we called it back in my day: “youtubing.” 🤣 Some of my silly videos caught on and I had a small community on the platform, but I always dreamed of being a big time YouTuber. Fast forward to today and I’m sitting here unboxing my first Youtube Creator Award for reaching 100,000 subscribers! 🏆 The full video is live on my YouTube (linked in bio) if you wanna see me get emotional! 🥲 Thanks for letting me share & celebrate my milestones with you! Your love & support keeps me motivated! 🧜🏼‍♀️💘
I’m holding in an exciting SEAcret! 🤭 There may or may not be a clue in this post… stay tuned!! 🧜🏼‍♀️💕 more news revealed this week!

I’m putting on my crown and heading out down to Mexico!! 🧜🏼‍♀️💦 I’ll be training and diving for the next several days to ensure I’m ready for an exciting opportunity to come! 🤭 I think a few of you already guessed it from my last post… 😜 anyway, my flight is tomorrow morning! I’ll do my best to share the adventures in my stories- and if I miss anything, I promise to document it in a tell-all post on the blog when I get back! ✈️

Feeling on top of the world after completing my mermaid training in Mexico and getting my advanced diver’s certification back at home! My first time in a cenote was as magical as I imagined and my first dive to 80ft was unexpectedly full of sea life! 🥹 It’s been a busy week of training and I still have one more course to go, but it will all be worth it come October 😁 stay tuned- I don’t think I can hold in this news much longer! 🫧

The mermaid grotto at @bbpiratefest was a hit! 😍 I poured my heart into this year’s tent, turning it into the mermaid wonderland I would want to visit as a kid! 🥹🧜🏼‍♀️🫧 

Guests could get a full mermaid makeover, from choosing hair charms that would get braided into their hair, to getting sparkling face gems! 

The clam throne got a facelift with some repairs and new foliage, so we were ready for all the shell-fies and all the intimate memories that are made in our photo booth! 

Last but not least, our newest addition was the mermaid splash pool with my brainchild- the “Pick a Pearl” game! Everyone loved going home with treasures, especially the lucky few who found black pearls and walked away with our biggest prizes!! ✨ 

I am so grateful for the opportunity to get creative with our mermaid offerings and am even more grateful for the talented team of mermaids and handlers who helped make this a possibility! We really made some magic together and I can’t wait to do it again soon! Stay tuned for more upcoming events like this! 🩷

Agave is the owner of this house! 🦈 We’re just swimming in it. 😮‍💨 Agave the Zebra shark was very interested in the mermaids who came to swim with her on the weekends in October, growing friendlier by the day. 😏 She clearly wanted a piece of the limelight and wasn’t afraid to cut us off for a little attention! 🤣 I can speak a little shark and could tell that she just wanted good girl scritches, but sadly we weren’t allowed to touch! 😋 Thanks for having me over, Agave! You have a lovely home!
.

social_posts.post_text: Mermaid at the Fairy Pools 🧜🏼‍♀️🧚🏼‍♀️ My Scotland trip feels so long ago, I can’t believe it was earlier this year! Seeing the mountains covered in snow was super magical!- It wasn’t my first time seeing snow or mountains, but Scotland’s views were like something I had only previously seen in a textbook. 🥹 Vast mountain ranges stacked as far as the eye can see, slinking into the sea at the coastline. While I feel like we did a decent job exploring the entire country on our 2 week roadtrip, I think it would be fun to visit again some day when the lands are greener and the waterfalls are warmer. 😍 What country is on your destination bucket list?

Went to the beach on a whim to film some Christmas content and met this sweet girl traveling with her family from Colombia! We collected shells and built a “snow” man in the sand together. I think this was a holiday she won’t soon forget and it was a warm reminder of why I started mermaiding- It’s all about the magic! 🥹🧜🏼‍♀️⛄️❤️
Warm wishes, merbabes! 😘🧜🏼‍♀️💦🎁

Merry Christmas Merfriends! 🧜🏼‍♀️🎄 I hope you all had a magical day filled with fun, food and family (of any kind!) 🥰 let me know in the comments if you got anything super cool this year! I need the deets! 🙈🎁 Sending all my love! 😘❤️
